						               													<description>The collection and assignment game for all Bob the Builder fans: Bob the Builder and his team face a huge task: A storm has caused damage throughout the city. Especially Bob's hall and the bridge got caught and they have to be repaired. The game is ideal for children between 3 and 6 years. The game material is flexible, for short or longer game rounds. The great 3D game structure invites small creative craftsmen to a free game. &amp;quot;Yo, we can do it!&amp;quot; call Bob and his team regularly in the popular TV series &amp;quot;Bob the Builder&amp;quot;. Children love the likeable master builder, who does all the work with determination and team spirit. And so it is clear that the little Bob fans also work together in the collection and assignment game &amp;quot;Bob the Builder Grossbaustelle&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Thanks to the simple rule of the game, children as young as 3 years of age can try their hand at being &amp;quot;great repairers&amp;quot; and repairing all damage to the structures by correctly allocating the construction cards and placing them in the right place. Whenever a player completes a building or construction phase, he receives a pawn as a reward. If all the cards are on the appropriate parts of the building, the players have managed and repaired the damage in the city together. Whoever has collected most of the pieces, can boast of being the &amp;quot;most industrious craftsman&amp;quot; and wins the game. In doing so, we will train for a good look and promote skill and creativity. The great game material is also ideal for free play. A fascinating collection and assignment game with great 3D game material made of cardboard.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
